1777603911472437	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3lg0		item.create	bn-23xn	{"description":"init.rs:87 uses Local::now() to name the initial shard, but shard.rs:1016 (current_year_month) uses Utc::now() for rotation/selection. Near month boundaries these disagree — local Apr 30 22:38 = UTC May 1, so init creates 2026-04.events while shard selection expects 2026-05. rotate_if_needed handles it by creating the new shard, but the inconsistency is unnecessary and confusing. Fix: switch init.rs to chrono::Utc::now() everywhere, matching the rest of the system. Update test expectations in init.rs:364 and init.rs:392.","kind":"task","title":"fix: use UTC consistently for shard naming in init"}	blake3:Adz-XHFhx4onOIBQlKmoesRwpfTEtksjW4a7rzzo-mM
