1778086583282788	bones-dev	itc:v3:AWKSZJkkk5JkmZMxAAAAQatWqrq1bWwAAAE3pg0		item.comment	bn-11vv	{"body":"## Implementation complete (option #1 + #2)\n\nCommitted in workspace bn-11vv as commit 1e7798ce.\n\n### Changes\n\n- crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/triage_support.rs:\n  - propagate_parent_blocked now returns PropagationResult { punt_suppressed, parent_block_origin }, where parent_block_origin maps each suppressed descendant to the nearest blocked-or-punted ancestor along its parent chain.\n  - TriageSnapshot exposes parent_block_origin and direct_blocker_counts (a pre-propagation snapshot of unresolved_blockers).\n  - Added BlockingAncestor + compute_blocking_ancestors + blocking_ancestor_reason helpers (top-5 by suppressed-descendant count, deterministic tiebreak by id).\n  - 3 new unit tests covering: nearest-ancestor recording on a 3-phase chain, aggregation/sort of compute_blocking_ancestors, and empty case.\n\n- crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/next.rs:\n  - Empty-state branch now emits structured advice naming the dominant ancestors and the count of leaves they suppress, in all three output modes.\n  - JSON shape: `{ message, bottlenecks: [BlockingAncestor...] }` with bottlenecks omitted when there's no propagation cause.\n\n- crates/bones-cli/src/cmd/triage.rs:\n  - New 'Blocking Ancestors' section between 'Blocked Hubs' and 'Quick Wins'.\n  - Text output adds 'blocking_ancestor' rows and an 'advice parent-blocked-chain ...' summary line when applicable.\n  - Existing internal tests updated for new build_rows / render_* signatures.\n\n### Verification\n\n- just check passes: fmt clean, clippy clean, 2556 tests passing.\n- Smoke-tested against ~/src/liveramp/crib/ws/crib2 — bn next now reports 42 suppressed leaves and lists the top 5 blocking ancestors (Phase 3, bn-bxy, Phase 1, Phase 4, Phase 11). bn triage shows them in the new section in both text and pretty modes.\n\n### What this does NOT change\n\n- The propagation rule itself is untouched. 'Goal A blocks goal B' still suppresses every descendant of B. Tests at children_of_blocked_goal_are_excluded_from_unblocked and deeply_nested_children_inherit_blocked_from_grandparent still hold. The user's choice to encode hard fences is preserved; we just point at which fence to open.\n\n### Ready for review\n\n@bones-reviewer — please review commit 1e7798ce in workspace bn-11vv."}	blake3:PadIzpR1yTVc8fiyzHARzO3GF6KvdM9r6lmy8jejhMo
